              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Use the algebra of sets to prove the conjecture from <xref ref="exer_sec43-setdiff"/>.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li xml:id="exer_sec43-6">
        <p>
          Let <m>A</m>, <m>B</m>,
          and <m>C</m> be subsets of some universal set <m>U</m>.
          <ol>
            <li xml:id="exer_sec43-setdiff2">
              <p>
                Draw two general Venn diagrams for the sets <m>A</m>, <m>B</m>,
                and <m>C</m>.
                On one, shade the region that represents <m>A - \left( {B \cap C} \right)</m>,
                and on the other,
                shade the region that represents <m>\left( {A - B} \right) \cup \left( {A - C} \right)</m>.
                Based on the Venn diagrams,
                make a conjecture about the relationship between the sets
                <m>A - \left( {B \cap C} \right)</m> and <m>\left( {A - B} \right) \cup \left( {A - C} \right)</m>.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Use the choose-an-element method to prove the conjecture from <xref ref="exer_sec43-setdiff2"/>.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Use the algebra of sets to prove the conjecture from <xref ref="exer_sec43-setdiff2"/>.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li xml:id="exer53_exer6">
        <p>
          Let <m>A</m>, <m>B</m>,
          and <m>C</m> be subsets of some universal set <m>U</m>.
          Prove or disprove each of the following:
          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>
                <m>\left( A \cap B \right) - C = \left( A - C \right) \cap \left( B - C \right)</m>
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                <m>\left( A \cup B \right) - \left( A \cap B \right) = \left( A - B \right) \cup \left(B - A \right)</m>
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li xml:id="exer_sec43-setdiff3x">
        <p>
          Let <m>A</m>, <m>B</m>,
          and <m>C</m> be subsets of some universal set <m>U</m>.
          <ol>
            <li xml:id="exer_sec43-setdiff3">
              <p>
                Draw two general Venn diagrams for the sets <m>A</m>, <m>B</m>,
                and <m>C</m>.
                On one, shade the region that represents <m>A - \left( {B - C} \right)</m>,
                and on the other,
                shade the region that represents <m>\left( {A - B} \right) - C</m>.
                Based on the Venn diagrams,
                make a conjecture about the relationship between the sets <m>A - \left( {B - C} \right)</m> and
